# Icon Guard - PLAT-692
# This file prevents icon regression by documenting icon requirements

## CRITICAL: DO NOT add icon.svg
Home Assistant icon loading priority:
1. icon.svg (HIGHEST - if exists, overrides PNG)
2. icon.png + icon@2x.png
3. brand/ subdirectory

The old orange SVG icon was removed in commit cd942fee.
If icon.svg exists, it will OVERRIDE the correct PNG icons.

## Required icon files:
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/icon.png (62224 bytes, MD5: de1a2e116b411dfa1d4da882774d7469)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/icon@2x.png (244539 bytes)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/logo.png (62224 bytes)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/logo@2x.png (244539 bytes)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/brand/icon.png (62224 bytes)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/brand/icon@2x.png (244539 bytes)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/brand/logo.png (62224 bytes)
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/brand/logo@2x.png (244539 bytes)

## FORBIDDEN files (will cause icon regression):
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/icon.svg
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/brand/icon.svg
- custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/icons/ (old subdirectory, removed)

## To verify icons after HA reload:
```bash
# Check no SVG exists
find custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh -name "*.svg" | wc -l  # Must be 0

# Verify PNG checksums
md5sum custom_components/tuya_ble_mesh/icon.png
# Expected: de1a2e116b411dfa1d4da882774d7469
```

## Cache clearing (if old icon persists):
If the old icon is still visible after reload:
1. Clear browser cache (Ctrl+Shift+R)
2. Restart Home Assistant: Developer Tools → Restart
3. Clear HA cache: `rm -rf /config/.storage/lovelace*`
4. Check integration: Settings → Devices & Services → Tuya BLE Mesh
